4. Troubleshooting


4.1: LED Safety Light Not Working


If the LED safety light on your Trailblazer Bike Helmet is not working, please follow the steps below to troubleshoot the issue:

1. Check the Battery: Ensure that the battery is properly installed and functional. Replace the battery if necessary with a CR2032 3V battery.

2. Inspect the Light: Examine the LED light to see if there are any visible signs of damage. If the light appears damaged, please contact Rugged Riders customer support for further assistance.</search_result>

2. Assembly and Adjustment


2.1: Attaching the LED Safety Light


To attach the LED safety light to your Trailblazer Bike Helmet, follow the steps below:

1. Locate the LED safety light - The LED safety light is located at the rear of the helmet, indicated by the "LED" label.

2. Insert the light - Insert the LED safety light into the corresponding slot at the back of the helmet, ensuring it is securely in place.

3. Turn on the light - Once attached, press the power button to turn on the LED safety light. The light will emit a bright, steady glow, enhancing your visibility during low-light conditions.</search_result>
